常春藤的学生很多都来自美国的东北部地区，特别是[[纽约|纽约]]、[[波士顿|波士顿]]，以及[[费城|费城]]地区。因为常春藤的八所学校都坐落于东北部，所以大多数学生从学校毕业之后就在东北部工作、生活，这也不足为奇。哈佛大学2013年发布的调查指出，42%来自东北部地区的学生，和55%的全体学生都计划在东北部定居。一直以来，[[纽约|纽约]]和[[波士顿|波士顿]]是毕业生工作生活的首选之地。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thecrimson.com/flash-graphic/2013/5/28/senior-survey-2013-graphic/|title=The Harvard Crimson|publisher=The Harvard Crimson, Inc.|accessdate=2014-10-08|archive-date=2013-06-23|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6HZufRXLV?url=http://www.thecrimson.com/flash-graphic/2013/5/28/senior-survey-2013-graphic/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/heres-where-ivy-league-students-go-when-they-graduate-presentation-2012-6?op=1|title=Here's Where Ivy League Students Go When They Graduate [Presentation]|date=2012-06-29|work=Business Insider|accessdate=2014-10-08|archive-date=2021-08-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210816112208/https://www.businessinsider.com/heres-where-ivy-league-students-go-when-they-graduate-presentation-2012-6?op=1}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theatlantic.com/business/archive/2012/02/why-do-so-many-ivy-league-grads-go-to-wall-steet/253245/|title=Why Do So Many Ivy League Grads Go to Wall Steet?|date=2012-02-17|work=The Atlantic|accessdate=2014-10-08|archive-date=2021-10-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211015132557/https://www.theatlantic.com/business/archive/2012/02/why-do-so-many-ivy-league-grads-go-to-wall-steet/253245/}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theamericanconservative.com/the-ivy-league-in-the-age-of-obama/|title=The Ivy League in the Age of Obama|work=The American Conservative|accessdate=2014-10-08|archive-date=2021-08-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210816112244/https://www.theamericanconservative.com/the-ivy-league-in-the-age-of-obama/}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.alternet.org/story/155535/the_best_and_the_greediest_ivy_league_students_are_still_heading_to_wall_street|title=The Best and the Greediest? Ivy League Students Ar